<br>
Yup. That's a very legitimate concern and I don't have a solution to it. I would call the post-heal instant if I could, but I don't think the spell engine allows that sort of thing.<br>
<br>
But. To put it in perspective... it's only 6 seconds. It's not like you would intentionally hit a 10khp mob with this, and then say &quot;quick guys! do 4khp more damage in the next 6 seconds and kill this mob before my spell collapses!&quot;.<br>
<br>
At most, this little loophole would allow someone else to finish the kill some of the time, if they got lucky.<br>
<br>
And with the double effect it wouldn't stack with itself. So two wizards couldn't team up to kill a 12khp mob with this spell. However if you landed this at the same time as Elnericks, you could kill an 8khp mob. I don't particularly see that as a problem...<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> This will never go live, becauce it would be the best spell to make exp.<br>
Look for mobs with less than 6k HP that are blue. one shot kills without any problems. Just boom, exp. trust me, never.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
True... it's easy. But one shot kills are about being easy. They have to be, in order to provide an emergency valve in dangerous situations.<br>
<br>
With Ice Comet I could one-shot many blue mobs in solB. It was easy, and it was fun as heck in groups, but it wasn't the most efficient time in my life as a wizard. I still chose quadding over Ice Comet when I was forced to solo, and got better efficiency even with CoF. <br>
<br>
It may be me, but I just don't see this as a tool wizards would use a lot when soloing, when they could be getting roughly 3x the efficiency in a quad kite. I guess if you were really worried you could make the nuke stun the wizard for a few seconds, which would really kill it in solo (resisted solo? you die.) but I was trying to get away from that line of thinking.<br>
<br>
Personally, I think the most problematic aspect of this spell design is the simple fact that it is a dual effect, and wizards have always been straightforward. But I also think that the real definition of the wizard class, is that we are not really about damage. Rogues are about damage; to us, it is just a method. Really, we are about making things <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> dead</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> when they need to be. And from that perspective I'm pretty happy with this idea. It forces that distinction. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulunaltoadsnatcher.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lunal Toadsnatcher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/16/02 9:01:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19622.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~bookfolk/_uimages/music4.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: not manaburn</span><hr size=1> Good spell idea, but I don't like having a heal as the mitigation, just because we don't heal as a class.  <br>
<br>
As you mentioned having a big time stun effect is pretty tired, but thats the one way I could see this spell being risky enough to justify the reward.  We get aggroed all the time, but if we get aggroed and can't get away or do anything about it that forces a wise decision in the spell's use.  <br>
